sentences: Luther Kent (born June 23, 1948) is an American blues singer based in New Orleans, Louisiana.
Kent now hosts a show that comes on Saturdays on WBRH called Luther’s House Party.
Kent now hosts a show that comes on Saturdays on WBRH called Luther’s House Party.
In 1948, Luther Kent was born Kent Rowell in New Orleans, Louisiana.
In 1970, he became the lead singer for a group named Cold Grits.
Kent joined Blood Sweat & Tears in 1974 and toured with them until the end of that same year.
Kent joined Blood Sweat & Tears in 1974 and toured with them until the end of that same year.
In 1977, Kent released his first solo album, World Class, on RCS Records, produced by Cy Frost at Abbey Road Studios in St. John's Wood, London, and Applewood Studios in Colorado.
In 1978, Kent and ex-Wayne Cochran musical director, Charlie Brent, formed Luther Kent & Trick Bag.
The band was active during the 1980s and 1990s, and released 3 CDs under the name.
Kent released a gospel album in 1996 teaming up with John Lee & the Heralds of Christ.
Kent toured Italy in 2006 with Italian blues guitarist Robi Zonca and his band.
The show was recorded and released as album Magic Box that year.
